Charlie, get your map out.
Find the directions to the hotel.

233
00:36:44,917 --> 00:36:47,713
- Don't you want a ride?
- We'll walk.

234
00:36:47,881 --> 00:36:54,679
I want a complete file on Sato,
and a report on what happened here.

235
00:36:54,846 --> 00:37:00,227
- Translate it by 09:00 tomorrow.
- Very well.

236
00:37:00,394 --> 00:37:03,022
Thank you.

237
00:37:03,189 --> 00:37:07,109
- Come on, Charlie.
- You will have a long walk.

238
00:37:07,277 --> 00:37:12,783
If I get lost, we'll call a cop.

239
00:37:12,950 --> 00:37:15,745
What?

240
00:37:25,547 --> 00:37:30,637
I know he didn't fill us in
on the gang war, but I like the guy.

241
00:37:30,804 --> 00:37:33,891
You told me it was four more blocks.

242
00:37:34,059 --> 00:37:41,273
- You said we'd walk home.
- I don't know where the hotel is.

243
00:37:41,441 --> 00:37:47,198
This isn't the time to ask you
what's going down with Oliver...

244
00:37:47,365 --> 00:37:52,245
Some suits back home
think I cut a deal with Sato.

245
00:37:52,411 --> 00:37:57,460
They're full of shit.
I'll back you up.

246
00:37:57,627 --> 00:38:01,172
What's going on here?

247
00:38:31,541 --> 00:38:36,797
What? What?
What is your problem?

248
00:38:52,856 --> 00:38:57,862
I don't know. We should cut our losses
and let the locals handle this one.

249
00:38:58,030 --> 00:39:01,491
I can't go back without him.

250
00:39:07,874 --> 00:39:13,463
Sato Kojo. He started as an enforcer
and rose quickly to minor boss.

251
00:39:15,340 --> 00:39:18,928
He controls some of the docks
and some construction in Hawaii.

252
00:39:21,013 --> 00:39:25,185
The victim last night
was one of Sato's guys.

253
00:39:25,352 --> 00:39:30,983
And six hours earlier,
Sato put a hit on this guy...

254
00:39:33,195 --> 00:39:38,116
- Okada Genkuro, an artist.
- He's an engraver.

255
00:39:38,283 --> 00:39:45,667
- 48 hours later he's in Scalari's.
- Who's this with Sato?

256
00:39:47,211 --> 00:39:50,380
Sugai Kunio. Top Oyabun.

257
00:39:50,547 --> 00:39:56,471
Like your Mafia bosses...
construction, gambling, extortion.

258
00:39:56,638 --> 00:40:00,977
- What's Sugai doing with Sato?
- I don't know.

259
00:40:01,143 --> 00:40:05,816
Even I know that Sato
used to work for Sugai.

260
00:40:05,982 --> 00:40:10,320
Now they're knocking each other off
left and right.

261
00:40:10,487 --> 00:40:13,991
These goddamn suits!

262
00:40:17,203 --> 00:40:20,623
- What's with the SWATs out here?
- Exercise.

263
00:40:20,790 --> 00:40:26,255
- Training perhaps.
- Come on, start cutting us in.

264
00:40:26,421 --> 00:40:32,137
I can't figure out what was in
that box in Scalari's. Drugs?

265
00:40:32,304 --> 00:40:38,602
No drugs. Steel, liquor, horses.

266
00:40:38,769 --> 00:40:42,733
He owns part ofthe Club Miyako.

267
00:40:47,613 --> 00:40:51,910
What's going on outside?

268
00:40:52,076 --> 00:40:56,373
They have a tip
about Sato's last hideout.

269
00:40:56,540 --> 00:40:59,543
- It's only a tip.
- It's only a tip?

270
00:40:59,709 --> 00:41:03,339
I promise I'll keep you informed.

271
00:41:05,133 --> 00:41:12,058
Could you find the file
on Sato's guy... Shinji Sekimitsu?

272
00:41:19,733 --> 00:41:23,237
Please, I need authorisation.

273
00:41:23,403 --> 00:41:27,743
No, it's a training exercise.

274
00:42:12,459 --> 00:42:15,088
- Observers.
- You got it.

275
00:42:37,739 --> 00:42:39,909
Observers.

276
00:42:53,090 --> 00:42:55,801
Is that the guy from the airport?

277
00:43:03,477 --> 00:43:05,395
That's him, right?

278
00:43:14,532 --> 00:43:17,159
Easy, Nicky.

279
00:43:23,291 --> 00:43:25,835
Hi, sweetheart.

280
00:43:27,420 --> 00:43:33,094
You remember me, don't you?
Where's your boss?

281
00:43:43,857 --> 00:43:48,654
- I only want to talk to him.
- What are you doing?

282
00:43:48,821 --> 00:43:52,701
This isn't New York.
We've got rules here.

283
00:43:52,867 --> 00:43:57,539
I've seen Sato's work.
He ain't following your programme.

284
00:43:57,705 --> 00:44:01,168
- You must have patience.
- Fuck patience.

285
00:44:15,226 --> 00:44:19,396
He was here. I know it.

286
00:44:29,618 --> 00:44:34,706
- We have to go.
- We're just observing.

287
00:44:34,872 --> 00:44:37,919
Can I take a quick look?

288
00:45:36,236 --> 00:45:38,989
Charlie.

289
00:45:46,122 --> 00:45:51,627
- I got something.
- Mas is in deep shit now.

290
00:46:12,652 --> 00:46:16,655
You don't want to eat that shit.
Give me a stick.

291
00:46:19,451 --> 00:46:24,624
- Son of a bitch!
- I always said you were the best.

292
00:46:24,790 --> 00:46:28,128
I owe you lunch.

293
00:46:59,872 --> 00:47:02,708
Where's Mas?

294
00:47:04,378 --> 00:47:08,466
Mas, we got good news for you.

295
00:47:08,633 --> 00:47:12,345
What the fuck's his problem?

296
00:47:20,730 --> 00:47:25,485
I will have no more to do with you.
Please, get out.

297
00:47:26,778 --> 00:47:32,118
- I know you took a little heat...
- Ohashi is waiting for you.

298
00:47:32,285 --> 00:47:36,540
- We'll square it.
- Let us explain what happened.

299
00:47:36,707 --> 00:47:43,172
You have dishonoured me
and our department. You are a thief.

300
00:47:48,052 --> 00:47:51,265
I saw you take the money.

301
00:47:54,143 --> 00:47:59,816
You saw me take the money...
I wanted to get things done.

302
00:47:59,983 --> 00:48:04,696
I have informed Ohashi.
He informed your captain.

303
00:48:04,864 --> 00:48:11,162
- We know what kind of man you are.
- You don't know one thing about me.

304
00:48:11,330 --> 00:48:15,542
You and your self-righteous bullshit
will cost me my job.

305
00:48:24,678 --> 00:48:27,431
If you pull it, you'd better use it.

306
00:48:31,353 --> 00:48:36,107
Watch this, okay?
I only want to do this once.

307
00:48:40,196 --> 00:48:44,618
Look, see how the impression
hardly leaves the ashes?

308
00:48:44,785 --> 00:48:47,913
There wasn't enough pressure.

309
00:48:48,080 --> 00:48:51,500
This is good, but this ain't money.

310
00:48:51,667 --> 00:48:57,883
The box contained samples or plates,
and this is a counterfeiting war.

311
00:48:58,049 --> 00:49:04,181
And you should talk to your partner
before you go to the suits.

312
00:49:05,224 --> 00:49:07,102
We were going to cut you in.

313
00:49:40,139 --> 00:49:44,936
Don't ever say you didn't have
a good time with Charlie Vincent.

314
00:49:50,901 --> 00:49:56,116
You know the American girl,
is she around tonight?

315
00:49:58,578 --> 00:50:02,290
Come here, baby. Join us.

316
00:50:02,457 --> 00:50:05,377
Come on.

317
00:50:09,173 --> 00:50:12,509
What is this?
It's still moving in my mouth.

318
00:50:14,345 --> 00:50:19,184
I haven't taken the silverware,
so just take a hike.

319
00:50:19,351 --> 00:50:23,940
Nicky, what are you doing?
Sit down. Join us.

320
00:50:24,105 --> 00:50:29,655
Superintendent Ohashi would
like to see you in the morning.

321
00:50:32,700 --> 00:50:38,581
Smoke a little peace pipe here.
We're all partners now.

322
00:50:38,747 --> 00:50:43,629
Mas, please join us.
We'll have a good time.

323
00:50:43,796 --> 00:50:47,716
- Come on.
- Thank you.

324
00:50:57,603 --> 00:51:03,318
Conklin, I did my duty.
These are the men I work for.

325
00:51:03,485 --> 00:51:07,740
You talk to your partners
before you go to the suits.

326
00:51:07,907 --> 00:51:12,912
You should think less of yourself
and more of your group.

327
00:51:13,078 --> 00:51:16,625
Try to work like a Japanese.

328
00:51:16,792 --> 00:51:21,005
I grew up with your soldiers.
You were wise then.

329
00:51:21,171 --> 00:51:25,968
Now, music and movies
are all that America is good for.

330
00:51:26,136 --> 00:51:31,058
We make the machines. We build
the future. We won the peace.

331
00:51:31,225 --> 00:51:37,523
Not one of you guys
has ever had an original idea.

332
00:51:37,690 --> 00:51:42,613
Are you guys
going to argue all the time?

333
00:51:42,780 --> 00:51:49,579
What is this, a conspiracy
to fuck up my evening?

334
00:51:49,746 --> 00:51:53,709
Mas, what are you doing?
It's good-time time.

335
00:51:53,877 --> 00:51:57,963
- Kampaitime.
- Up and down.

336
00:52:19,697 --> 00:52:22,617
Can I talk to you?

337
00:52:22,784 --> 00:52:27,999
Look, I need your help.
I've got my tits in the wringer.

338
00:52:28,166 --> 00:52:32,045
Just talk to me
for a couple of minutes.

339
00:52:32,211 --> 00:52:38,344
Give that woman down there $50
and go where she takes you.

340
00:52:52,318 --> 00:52:57,991
Show a little mercy,
some people are trying to eat.

341
00:52:58,157 --> 00:53:02,289
- You like that stuff?
- Yes.

342
00:53:02,455 --> 00:53:06,751
"That's Amore".
I was a teenager when it was new.

343
00:53:06,918 --> 00:53:11,047
I was a teenager when it was old.

344
00:53:11,214 --> 00:53:16,179
If you're going to hang around with
NYPD, here's what you have to do.

345
00:53:16,345 --> 00:53:21,434
Lose that tie, it's a fire hazard.
Here's a little gift.

346
00:53:21,602 --> 00:53:26,733
Straight from the Big Apple,
from Charlie Vincent to you.

347
00:53:29,777 --> 00:53:32,989
- Thanks.
- It's my honour.

348
00:53:34,115 --> 00:53:36,785
I like you.

349
00:53:36,952 --> 00:53:40,873
- Top drawer, yes?
- Top drawer.

350
00:53:42,292 --> 00:53:46,796
Hey, meatball, what are you doing?
You can't hit a note.

351
00:53:49,467 --> 00:53:52,971
- You could do better?
- Yes, I could do better.

352
00:53:53,138 --> 00:53:57,475
- Put it up or shut it up.
- To you, from me.

353
00:54:04,692 --> 00:54:07,821
- Thank you.
- Don't quit your day job.

354
00:54:16,206 --> 00:54:20,418
That quick?
What's he talking about?

355
00:54:44,989 --> 00:54:47,534
Ray Charles.

356
00:54:48,368 --> 00:54:50,620
You and me.

357
00:54:52,957 --> 00:54:55,417
Detective, wait.

358
00:54:55,583 --> 00:55:00,131
Masahiro Matsumoto,
ladies and gentlemen.

359
00:55:26,328 --> 00:55:28,663
Masahiro Matsumoto!

360
00:55:31,959 --> 00:55:34,963
If you're looking for Sato,
I can't help you.

361
00:55:35,129 --> 00:55:38,008
He hasn't been here in over a year.

362
00:55:38,175 --> 00:55:42,763
- Who did he do regularly?
- Do you think I pay attention?

363
00:55:42,929 --> 00:55:48,144
You'd recognise if one of your
customers had a different tie on.

364
00:55:51,898 --> 00:55:57,697
He had a different girl every time.
I didn't know of anybody regular.

365
00:55:57,864 --> 00:56:03,287
That's Sugai and the girl in sequins
is the one with blood on her hands.

366
00:56:03,453 --> 00:56:07,833
- You did your homework.
- How do I get to him?

367
00:56:08,000 --> 00:56:13,006
I've been living in this country
for seven years...

368
00:56:13,173 --> 00:56:17,260
I still can't read the headlines.

369
00:56:17,427 --> 00:56:20,139
How do I get to him?

370
00:56:20,306 --> 00:56:25,103
Let the police handle it.
No one's going to help a gaijin.

371
00:56:25,270 --> 00:56:31,360
A stranger. A foreigner.
Me and you... more you.

372
00:56:39,786 --> 00:56:42,580
- Got to go.
- Hold on.

373
00:56:42,747 --> 00:56:47,296
- Wrigley Field has lights now.
- Yeah, Mom told me.

374
00:56:47,463 --> 00:56:53,052
Did she? Did she say it's not stupid
to be scared?

375
00:56:53,219 --> 00:56:56,347
But sometimes
you've got to choose a side.

376
00:56:56,514 --> 00:57:01,269
I did. I'm on my side.

377
00:57:31,972 --> 00:57:36,018
- The drinks cost $1 25.
- How much was the fish?

378
00:57:36,185 --> 00:57:40,314
- $200.
- Holy shit!

379
00:57:40,481 --> 00:57:44,653
How much would it have been
if it was cooked? Did you pay?

380
00:57:44,820 --> 00:57:51,369
No, Matsumoto signed it over
to the Osaka Police Department.

381
00:57:51,535 --> 00:57:55,749
That's the best thing
he's done for us. You like the guy?

382
00:57:55,917 --> 00:58:00,546
- Mas? He's okay.
- Who the hell's this?

383
00:58:07,596 --> 00:58:10,975
I can't figure this place out.

384
00:58:13,227 --> 00:58:16,730
You want to play?
You and me, come on.

385
00:58:16,897 --> 00:58:19,193
Right here.

386
00:58:20,402 --> 00:58:23,155
That's it. Hey!

387
00:58:23,322 --> 00:58:26,742
- Fuck!
- Good move.

388
00:58:30,747 --> 00:58:35,628
Good. Bring it back.
We'll go again.

389
00:58:35,795 --> 00:58:39,965
Bring it back... Did you see that?

390
00:58:40,133 --> 00:58:45,180
- Don't get personal.
- Fuck you!

391
00:58:45,347 --> 00:58:51,061
- Charlie, it's only a coat.
- He's got my passport.

392
00:58:51,229 --> 00:58:58,112
- Jesus Christ.
- Come here, you little fuck.

393
00:59:00,072 --> 00:59:03,410
Charlie!

394
00:59:34,391 --> 00:59:37,811
Charlie!

395
00:59:38,979 --> 00:59:43,194
Come here!
Fuck!

396
00:59:50,993 --> 00:59:54,957
You little shit.

397
00:59:55,123 --> 00:59:59,336
Stay there, you little shit.

398
00:59:59,503 --> 01:00:04,967
You little shit!

